# ðŸŽ¯ Project: Library Management System with OOP
# Build a comprehensive library management system using Object-Oriented Programming principles. Create Book, Member, and Library classes to manage book borrowing, returns, and tracking. This project will teach you how to design and implement real-world systems using classes and objects.

# ðŸ› ï¸ Technical Requirements:
# Create Book class with attributes (title, author, ISBN, availability)
# Create Member class with attributes (name, member_id, borrowed_books)
# Create Library class to manage books and members
# Implement methods for borrowing and returning books
# Add search functionality for books
# Implement due date tracking and overdue calculations
# Add data persistence using file operations
# Create a user-friendly menu system
# ðŸ“‹ Step-by-Step Guide:
# Step 1: Design Class Structure
# â€¢ Plan the attributes and methods for each class
# â€¢ Define relationships between classes
# â€¢ Create UML diagram or class structure sketch
# Step 2: Implement Book Class
# â€¢ Create Book class with __init__ method
# â€¢ Add attributes: title, author, isbn, year, available (boolean)
# â€¢ Add __str__ method for readable representation
# â€¢ Add methods: check_out(), return_book()
# Step 3: Implement Member Class
# â€¢ Create Member class with __init__ method
# â€¢ Add attributes: name, member_id, borrowed_books (list)
# â€¢ Add methods: borrow_book(), return_book()
# â€¢ Add maximum borrow limit (e.g., 5 books)
# Step 4: Implement Library Class
# â€¢ Create Library class to manage collections
# â€¢ Add attributes: books (dictionary), members (dictionary)
# â€¢ Add methods: add_book(), remove_book(), find_book()
# â€¢ Add methods: register_member(), find_member()
# Step 5: Implement Core Functionality
# â€¢ Add borrow_book() method in Library class
# â€¢ Add return_book() method with overdue calculation
# â€¢ Implement search by title, author, or ISBN
# â€¢ Add statistics: total books, available books, etc.
# Step 6: Add File Operations
# â€¢ Save/load books to JSON file
# â€¢ Save/load members to JSON file
# â€¢ Implement backup functionality
# â€¢ Handle file errors gracefully
# Step 7: Create User Interface
# â€¢ Build a menu system for librarians
# â€¢ Add input validation for all operations
# â€¢ Create formatted displays for books and members
# â€¢ Add search results display
# ðŸ’» Sample Code:
